{"id":740,"parent_id":702,"book_id":1,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":740,"title":"Isaiah 38","subtitle":"","short_title":"Isa.","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/38","content":[["div",[".titleNumber","Chapter 38"],[".studySummary",["i","Hezekiah’s life is lengthened fifteen years—The sun goes back ten degrees as a sign—Hezekiah praises and thanks the Lord."]]],[".bodyBlock",["div",{"id":"1","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/38.1","order":"02.24.038.47980"},["b","1"],"In those days was",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_1a"},"Hezekiah"],"sick unto death. And Isaiah the prophet the son of Amoz came unto him, and said unto him, Thus saith the",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],", Set thine house in order: for thou shalt die, and not live."],["div",{"id":"2","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/38.2","order":"02.24.038.47981"},["b","2"],"Then Hezekiah turned his face toward the wall, and prayed unto the",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],","],["div",{"id":"3","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/38.3","order":"02.24.038.47982"},["b","3"],"And said, Remember now, O",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],", I beseech thee, how I have walked before thee in truth and with a perfect heart, and have done",["i","that which is"],"good in thy sight. And Hezekiah wept sore."],["div",{"id":"4","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/38.4","order":"02.24.038.47983"},["b","4"],"¶Then came the word of the",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],"to Isaiah, saying,"],["div",{"id":"5","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/38.5","order":"02.24.038.47984"},["b","5"],"Go, and say to Hezekiah, Thus saith the",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],", the God of David thy father, I have heard thy prayer, I have seen thy tears: behold, I will",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_5a"},"add"],"unto thy days fifteen years."],["div",{"id":"6","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/38.6","order":"02.24.038.47985"},["b","6"],"And I will deliver thee and this city out of the hand of the king of Assyria: and I will",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_6a"},"defend"],"this city."],["div",{"id":"7","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/38.7","order":"02.24.038.47986"},["b","7"],"And this",["i","shall be"],"a sign unto thee from the",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],", that the",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],"will do this thing that he hath spoken;"],["div",{"id":"8","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/38.8","order":"02.24.038.47987"},["b","8"],"Behold, I will bring again the",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_8a"},"shadow"],"of the degrees, which is gone down in the sun dial of Ahaz, ten degrees backward. So the",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_8b"},"sun"],"returned ten degrees, by which degrees it was gone down."],["div",{"id":"9","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/38.9","order":"02.24.038.47988"},["b","9"],"¶The",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_9a"},"writing"],"of Hezekiah king of Judah, when he had been sick, and was recovered of his sickness:"],["div",{"id":"10","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/38.10","order":"02.24.038.47989"},["b","10"],"I said in the cutting off of my days, I shall go to the gates of the grave: I am deprived of the residue of my years."],["div",{"id":"11","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/38.11","order":"02.24.038.47990"},["b","11"],"I said, I shall not see the",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],",",["i","even"],"the",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],", in the land of the living: I shall behold man no more with the inhabitants of the world."],["div",{"id":"12","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/38.12","order":"02.24.038.47991"},["b","12"],"Mine age is departed, and is removed from me as a shepherd’s tent: I have",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_12a"},"cut off"],"like a weaver my life: he will cut me off",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_12b"},"with pining sickness"],": from day",["i","even"],"to night wilt thou make an end of me."],["div",{"id":"13","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/38.13","order":"02.24.038.47992"},["b","13"],"I reckoned till morning,",["i","that,"],"as a lion, so will he break all my bones: from day",["i","even"],"to night wilt thou make an end of me."],["div",{"id":"14","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/38.14","order":"02.24.038.47993"},["b","14"],"Like a crane",["i","or"],"a swallow, so did I chatter: I did mourn as a dove: mine eyes fail",["i","with looking"],"upward: O",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],", I am oppressed;",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_14a"},"undertake for me"],"."],["div",{"id":"15","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/38.15","order":"02.24.038.47994"},["b","15"],"What shall I say? he hath both spoken unto me, and himself hath done",["i","it:"],"I shall go softly all my years in the",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_15a"},"bitterness"],"of my soul."],["div",{"id":"16","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/38.16","order":"02.24.038.47995"},["b","16"],"O Lord, by these",["i","things men"],"live, and in all these",["i","things is"],"the life of my spirit:",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_16a"},"so"],"wilt thou recover me, and make me to live."],["div",{"id":"17","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/38.17","order":"02.24.038.47996"},["b","17"],"Behold,",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_17a"},"for"],"peace I had great bitterness: but thou hast in love to my soul",["i",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_17b"},"delivered"],"it"],"from the pit of corruption: for thou hast cast all my sins behind thy back."],["div",{"id":"18","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/38.18","order":"02.24.038.47997"},["b","18"],"For the grave cannot praise thee, death can",["i","not"],"celebrate thee: they that go down into the pit cannot hope for thy truth."],["div",{"id":"19","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/38.19","order":"02.24.038.47998"},["b","19"],"The living, the living, he shall praise thee, as I",["i","do"],"this day: the",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_19a"},"father"],"to the children shall make known thy",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_19b"},"truth"],"."],["div",{"id":"20","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/38.20","order":"02.24.038.47999"},["b","20"],"The",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],["i","was ready"],"to save me: therefore we will sing my songs to the stringed instruments all the days of our life in the house of the",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],"."],["div",{"id":"21","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/38.21","order":"02.24.038.48000"},["b","21"],"For Isaiah had said, Let them take a lump of figs, and",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_21a"},"lay",["i","it"]],"for a plaster upon the",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_21b"},"boil"],", and he shall recover."],["div",{"id":"22","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/38.22","order":"02.24.038.48001"},["b","22"],"Hezekiah also had said, What",["i","is"],"the sign that I shall go up to the house of the",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],"?"]]],"refs":[["div",{"id":"1a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/38.1a","order":"02.24.038.48002"},["b","1a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/20.1.1-6,9-11"},"2 Kgs. 20:1 (1–6, 9–11)"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-chr/32.32"},"2 Chr. 32:32"],"."],["div",{"id":"5a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/38.5a","order":"02.24.038.48004"},["b","5a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/42.48"},"D&C 42:48"],".",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/benevolence"},"TG Benevolence"],"."],["div",{"id":"6a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/38.6a","order":"02.24.038.48006"},["b","6a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/isa/37.35"},"Isa. 37:35"],"."],["div",{"id":"8a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/38.8a","order":"02.24.038.48008"},["b","8a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/20.10.9-10"},"2 Kgs. 20:10 (9–10)"],"."],["div",{"id":"8b","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/38.8b","order":"02.24.038.48010"},["b","8b"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/josh/10.12.12-14"},"Josh. 10:12 (12–14)"],"."],["div",{"id":"9a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/38.9a","order":"02.24.038.48012"},["b","9a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/scriptures-writing-of"},"TG Scriptures, Writing of"],"."],["div",{"id":"12a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/38.12a","order":"02.24.038.48014"},["b","12a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/job/14.2.1-2"},"Job 14:2 (1–2)"],"."],["div",{"id":"12b","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/38.12b","order":"02.24.038.48016"},["b","12b"],["span.small","OR"],"as a dangling thread; i.e., when a weaver has finished weaving a piece of cloth, he rolls it up to cut it off the loom."],["div",{"id":"14a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/38.14a","order":"02.24.038.48018"},["b","14a"],["span.small","HEB"],"be my security."],["div",{"id":"15a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/38.15a","order":"02.24.038.48020"},["b","15a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/job/10.1"},"Job 10:1"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/7.44.42-44"},"Moses 7:44 (42–44)"],"."],["div",{"id":"16a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/38.16a","order":"02.24.038.48022"},["b","16a"],["span.small","HEB"],"restore me."],["div",{"id":"17a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/38.17a","order":"02.24.038.48024"},["b","17a"],["span.small","OR"],"on my peace came great bitterness."],["div",{"id":"17b","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/38.17b","order":"02.24.038.48026"},["b","17b"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/27.29.28-30"},"Mosiah 27:29 (28–30)"],"."],["div",{"id":"19a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/38.19a","order":"02.24.038.48028"},["b","19a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ps/145.4"},"Ps. 145:4"],"."],["div",{"id":"19b","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/38.19b","order":"02.24.038.48030"},["b","19b"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ps/78.4.2-4"},"Ps. 78:4 (2–4)"],"."],["div",{"id":"21a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/38.21a","order":"02.24.038.48032"},["b","21a"],["span.small","HEB"],"smear it on."],["div",{"id":"21b","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/38.21b","order":"02.24.038.48034"},["b","21b"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/job/2.7"},"Job 2:7"],"."]]}
